    <div class="documentBody">
        
        <div>
            <p>Anniken Huitfeldt was appointed Minister of Culture on 20 October 2009. Before that she has been Minister of Children and Equality from 2008-2009. Since 2005, Anniken Huitfeldt has been a Member of Parliament for the Labour Party for Akershus County. She was a deputy member in the 2001 – 2005 and 1993 – 1997 parliamentary terms. Ms. Huitfeldt was a researcher with the Institute for Labour and Social Research, FAFO, from 2000 to 2005. She was President of the Labour Youth League from 1996 to 2000, and has headed the Norwegian Labour Party women’s network since 2007. Ms Huitfeldt holds a postgraduate degree in History from the University of Oslo and has completed undergraduate studies in Political Science and Geography. She was a student at the London School of Economics from 1992 to 1993. </p>
<p><strong>Education:</strong> <br />1993–1996 &nbsp;Postgraduate degree in History, University of Oslo&nbsp; <br />1992–1993 &nbsp;Undergraduate studies in Geography, London School of Economics <br />1989–1992 &nbsp;Undergraduate studies in Political Science and History, University of Oslo </p>
<p><strong>Political posts:</strong> <br />2008-2009 - Minister of Children and Equality<br />2007– &nbsp;Head of the Norwegian Labour Party women’s network<br />2005– &nbsp;First Deputy Chair of the Standing Committee Education, Research and Church Affairs<br />2005– &nbsp;Member of the Labour Party Parliamentary Group&nbsp; <br />2002– &nbsp;Member of the Labour Party Central Executive Committee <br /><br /><strong>Other posts:</strong> <br />2003–2005&nbsp;Member of the Board of the Norwegian Organisation for Asylum Seekers (NOAS)<br />2001–2003&nbsp;Member of the Commission on Quality in Basic Education <br />2001–2007&nbsp;Member of the Board of Save the Children Norway <br />2000–2005&nbsp;Researcher at the Institute for Applied Social Science FAFO<br />2000–2005&nbsp;Member of the Board for Falstad Memorial and Human Rights Centre<br />2000–2002&nbsp;Member of the Housing Commission<br />2000–2001&nbsp;Vice-President of the International Union of Socialist Youth<br />2000&nbsp;&nbsp;President of the Nordic Socialist Youth League <br />1996–2000&nbsp;President of the Labour Youth League<br />1994–1996&nbsp;Vice-President of the Labour Youth League<br />1990–1994&nbsp;Member of the Board of the Labour Youth League<br />1989–1995&nbsp;Member of School Committee in Akershus County <br />1988–1989 &nbsp;Secretary of the Labour Youth League, Akershus County <br />1987–1991&nbsp;Member of the Gender Equality Committee, Ullensaker municipality<br />1987–1989&nbsp;Member of the Commission for General Education Subjects<br />1987–1988&nbsp;Member of the Central Executive Committee of the Norwegian School Students’ Union (NGS) <br />1986–1988&nbsp;Student representative, Akershus County School Board, 1986–1988<br />1986–1990&nbsp;Member of the Board, Akershus Labour Youth League<br />1985–1988&nbsp;President of the Labour Youth League, Ullensaker municipality</p>
<p><strong>Other work experience:</strong> <br />County Secretary, Akershus Labour Youth League, 1988–1989 <br />Researcher at the Institute for Applied Social Science FAFO, 2000–2005</p>
